  "guidance": [
    "Use round 8 professional cards as the default visual grammar: title, technical name, context rail, field semantics, and micro-telemetry.",
    "Drive release readiness through the promotion board instead of ad-hoc canvas inspection.",
    "Keep firewall, compatibility and blocker posture visible in every review lane.",
    "Use focus decks as the default executive navigation model for large manufacturing graphs.",
    "Treat observability tiles as performance governance for canvas, search, inspector and registry freshness.",
    "Promote through explicit branch topology: main → preview → release_candidate → production/hotfix.",
    "Assign owner, steward and approver metadata across all operational domains.",
    "Bind workflow contracts to order, inspection, CAPA, document/training and equipment flows.",
    "Use storyboards as saved review views for architecture board, manufacturing leaders and compliance auditors.",
    "Treat hotspot tables as platform hubs and harden their metadata, policies and view presets first.",
    "Model PostgreSQL-native objects as first-class surfaces: views, materialized views, functions, procedures, event triggers, schemas, and roles.",
    "Use the atlas mesh to balance physical coverage with governance boards, export surfaces, and traceability views.",
    "Make workspace default to a seeded canonical design so reports never render empty in first-run environments.",
    "Treat export bundles as governance artifacts: DBML, Mermaid, PlantUML, manifest, typed diff, SQL plan, and release notes must stay aligned.",
    "Review changes through role-aware modes so architects, quality managers, compliance leads, and builders read the same source of truth differently."
  ],
